The paper deals with the optimization of information retrieval systems, which is a core topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). The optimization is done using loss functions, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also applies the optimization to vision tasks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The algorithm presented in the paper is based on quicksort, which is a sorting algorithm and falls under data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses a direct-loss minimization framework, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
